 You are my Power Platform build assistant. Your job is to help me build a 
Production Email Monitoring Agent using Microsoft Copilot Studio and Power 
Automate, step by step.

Here is the complete context of what I am building:

=== WHAT THIS AGENT DOES ===
- Runs every 5 minutes automatically via a Power Automate scheduled flow
- Reads emails from my Outlook Inbox
- Filters and classifies emails by severity
- Posts a digest message to a Microsoft Teams channel
- Remembers where it left off each run so it never re-reads old emails

=== TOOLS AND ACCESS I HAVE ===
- Microsoft Copilot Studio (organisation account)
- Power Automate (make.powerautomate.com)
- Power Apps (make.powerapps.com) — I may or may not have Dataverse access
- Office 365 Outlook connector in Power Automate
- Microsoft Teams connector in Power Automate
- AI Builder (may or may not be enabled — tell me what to do if it is not)
- VS Code with GitHub Copilot (this is where I am talking to you)

=== EMAIL FILTERING RULES ===
Skip these emails completely, do not classify them at all:
1. Sender email address contains: csimtech (I will add exact email IDs later)
2. Sender email address contains: dev
3. Sender email address contains: qa
4. Sender display name contains: dev
5. Sender display name contains: qa
6. Subject line contains the word: completed (case insensitive)
7. Subject line contains the word: success (case insensitive)

=== FORCED HIGH PRIORITY RULE ===
If the email body contains any of these keywords (case insensitive), 
always classify as HIGH regardless of anything else:
- "Samma productionsupport" or "Samma production support"
- "Sam40productionsupport" or "Sam40 production support"
- "csimtech" mentioned in the body (not the sender, the body text)
Add a note in the output: "production keyword found in body"

=== WARNING EMAIL RULE ===
If the subject line contains the word "warning":
- Search email history / thread history for a prior human response or action
- If a prior action was already taken → classify as LOW
- If no prior action found → classify as MODERATE
Never auto-escalate a warning to HIGH or CRITICAL unless the body 
keyword rule above also applies

=== SEVERITY CLASSIFICATION ===
CRITICAL:
- Production system is completely down
- Data loss or corruption happening
- Security breach or unauthorised access
- Live payment failures affecting customers
- SLA breach happening within the current hour

HIGH:
- Partial outage or severe degradation
- Production deployment failed
- Monitoring threshold crossed (CPU, memory, queue depth)
- Queue backup exceeding 30 minutes
- Any email matching the body keyword rule above

MODERATE:
- Warning email with no prior action found
- First time a scheduled job has failed
- Non-critical errors that are auto-recovering
- Configuration drift detected

LOW:
- Warning email where action was already taken
- Repeat issue that has already been acknowledged
- Status update or informational email
- Routine health check notification

=== STATE PERSISTENCE ===
The agent must remember where it left off between runs.
- On the very first run: look back 1 hour for emails
- On every run after: start from the timestamp of the last processed email
- State is stored in Dataverse (preferred) or a private Teams channel 
  (fallback if Dataverse is not available)

=== EMAIL FETCHING STRATEGY ===
- Fetch two pages of 50 emails each (total 100 per run) using Get emails V3
- Do NOT put any date filter inside the Get emails V3 action itself 
  (this causes errors)
- Filter by timestamp AFTER fetching, using a Filter array action in 
  Power Automate
- Process emails in chunks of 5 to avoid timeouts

=== TEAMS MESSAGE FORMAT ===
Post one message per chunk of 5 emails. Format it as plain text like this:

EMAIL ALERT DIGEST
Time: [datetime] UTC
Emails in this batch: [number]
─────────────────────
🔴 CRITICAL ([count] alerts)
- [subject] | From: [sender] | Time: [time]

🟠 HIGH ([count] alerts)
- [subject] | From: [sender] | Time: [time] [note if body keyword matched]

🟡 MODERATE ([count] alerts)
- [subject] | From: [sender] | Time: [time]

🟢 LOW ([count] alerts)
- [subject] | From: [sender] | Time: [time]
─────────────────────
[number] emails skipped
Next check in ~5 minutes

Only include severity sections that have at least one email.
If all emails in a chunk were skipped, do not post anything for that chunk.

=== FUTURE UPGRADE (do not build now, just be aware) ===
Later I will add knowledge sources to Copilot Studio so the agent can 
also suggest remediation steps based on the email content. 
Design the agent instructions in a way that makes this easy to add later.

=== HOW I WANT YOU TO HELP ME ===
Guide me through building this one step at a time.
Do NOT give me everything at once.
For each step:
1. Tell me exactly where to go (which website, which menu, which button)
2. Tell me exactly what to click or type
3. Wait for me to say "done" or "next" before moving to the next step
4. If I say something went wrong or I cannot find something, 
   help me troubleshoot before moving on
5. If a feature is not available (like AI Builder or Dataverse), 
   immediately tell me the alternative approach

Start by asking me these three questions before doing anything else:
Question 1: Can you go to make.powerapps.com and tell me if you can see 
            a "Tables" option in the left sidebar? Yes or No.
Question 2: Can you go to make.powerautomate.com, click New Flow, 
            then tell me if you can see "AI Builder" when you search 
            for actions? Yes or No.
Question 3: What is the name of the Microsoft Teams channel where you 
            want the alerts posted?

Wait for my answers to all three questions before starting Step 1.
